                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/97: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-18T15:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 8.26 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s February 13, 6 p.m. Nicaraguan Minister for Foreign Affairs sent a
                    telegram to Honduranean Government under date of January 28th last in which he
                    informed that Government that the Gutierrez Pena timber concession had been
                    annulled and the only timber cutting is in zone occupied by Nicaragua as per
                    agreement previous to May 20, 1918.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
